19:
I will perform miracles in the sky above
and wonders on the earth below.
There will be blood, fire, and thick smoke;

25:
For David said about him:
‘I saw the Lord before me at all times;
he is near me, and I will not be troubled.

31:
David saw what God was going to do in the future, and so he spoke about the resurrection of the Messiah when he said:
‘He was not abandoned in the world of the dead;
his body did not rot in the grave.’

25:
By means of the Holy Spirit you spoke through our ancestor David, your servant, when he said:
‘Why were the Gentiles furious;
why did people make their useless plots?

32-33:
And we are here to bring the Good News to you: what God promised our ancestors he would do, he has now done for us, who are their descendants, by raising Jesus to life. As it is written in the second Psalm:
‘You are my Son;
today I have become your Father.’
